HDB resale prices rise for 8th straight month  up 2.4% in Q11. HOUSING Board (HDB) resale prices rose for the eighth consecutive quarter in Q1 2022  up 2.4 per cent from Q4 2021  HDB announced on Friday (Apr 22).2. This came despite lower transaction volume  which fell 12.7 per cent quarter on quarter to 6 934 cases. Compared to the Q1 2021  transactions fell by 8.5 per cent.3. Fridayâ€™s price growth was slightly higher than the estimated 2.3 per cent that HDB had released on Apr 1.
